In life there are images that are so important that you randomly think about little sections of color or textures or the way a line bends, they inspire us and part of our subconscious creativity. Sometimes it is just a logo and sometimes it is a complex piece of art like this enormous painting made by Kiki. This painting I have been getting lost in for almost a decade now, in my life this symbolizes me leaving my country for the first time and coming to a city in Germany and met friends that feel like family that are willing to work hard with me and share the best of laughs. I feel at home somewhere thousands of miles away from where I am from. Kiki and his artwork and his work ethic and his heart has opened up a world to be I never dreamed of. So THIS is one of the most important images I have ever seen in my life and this place and these people I call my friends have impacted my life in a way that thanks yous don’t even begin to express my gratitude. Thank you Bremen Germany and everyone that has shared a laugh or a pizza or genuine good time with while here and Kiki thank you for being. Such an amazing positive light in my life!

Painted til I fell asleep, started again as soon as I woke up. I’ve been creating tons of work I haven’t shared yet so here’s a little skully skull I painted to get this week started!! There is inspiration all around us every day…most people see the same scenery every day and it all starts to blur together and you lose focus of the little things to discover that are right in front of you. There is always something right beside you that you overlook and take for granted. Take the time to appreciate the small stuff and try to seek out at least one small thing every day that is different and new… break your routine and take a different route you have never taken, say hello to strangers when you pass them on the street, try some new food that you never thought to try, explore new music, be open to things outside of your comfort zone….. get weird, shake yer buttcheeks and HAVE FUN DAMNIT!! Life is completely awesome so don’t take your day for granted… every day we open our eyes we have a new opportunity to change the things we didn’t like about yesterday and enter the day with a new perspective and the chance to be a better person than every day behind us!
Defenders Of Good Times for life!!!

Life in Bremen has been nothing short of amazing! I put my heart into my work and into friendships that although fresh in time feel like that have been with me my entire life! Kiki has been like a brother to me for over a decade and has stood by my side through the good and the bad and now he has given me the opportunity to come to Germany to work together so we can bring new life and energy to the city of Bremen. We have proven that no matter what we can make shit happen and continue to hype up our friends, inspire people to also create and pass on the good times to as others. None of this would be possible without the open minds and open hearts of those surrounding us. This studio is such a special building that has connected many of creative minds and to build these walls and hang these paintings with Kiki to share with you is an honor. Our studio consists of Kiki, Max, Carl and Peter who are all good hearted, hard working, driven individuals who have become such close friends to me and shared so many amazing conversations about reality and beyond and that is so special to me that I can’t put it into words. I could go on for days about my friends here and how grateful I am to live my days here and be able to paint everyday and share my bright ideas with the community but I’ll sum it all up with I LOVE BREMEN! My heart is here in a genuine way and I look forward to all the future memories I get to make with y’all in this city! THANK YOU to everyone who came out to my exhibition and shared the good times this weekend! Today is the last day the walls will be up and I am here all day so just send me a message if you would like to stop by and see the show before it’s down!!
Be yourself, be weird, shake yer buttcheeks and HAVR FUN DAMNIT! Life is completely awesome… every single tiny moment so don’t take your time here for granted, don’t let your fears hold you back from anything, take risks and allow yourself to be in uncomfortable situations so that you can actually live and learn and adapt! 
Defenders Of Good Times forever until the day we die!
